        <num>7-6-2</num>
        <content>
          <p>Any person denied a loan or credit solely on the basis of discrimination because of sex, race, religion, national origin, or marital status shall have a right to bring an action for damages in any court of competent jurisdiction in an individual, but not in a representative, capacity against the person, firm, or corporation violating this chapter.</p>
          <p>(Ga. L. 1975, p. 772, ยง 2.)</p>
